# Security headers applied by Cloudflare Pages to every response.
#
# The resource CSP (script-src + its inline-bootstrap hash, style-src,
# font-src, connect-src, img-src, base-uri) is emitted as a <meta> CSP by
# SvelteKit — see web/svelte.config.js (kit.csp, hash mode). It lives there
# because the inline-script hash is recomputed on every build.
#
# `frame-ancestors` cannot be expressed in a <meta> CSP, so the anti-clickjacking
# policy lives here as a real header (with X-Frame-Options for old browsers).
/*
  Content-Security-Policy: frame-ancestors 'none'
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
